DataType.Description: defines flags for the category of explosion protection for devices according to EU Directive 2014/34/EU (ATEX)

Field.Name: M1
Field.Description: This category is intended for use in underground mines and their surface installations which may be endangered by firedamp and/or combustible dust. Category 1 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a very high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: M2
Field.Description: This category is intended for use in underground mines and their surface installations which may be endangered by firedamp and/or combustible dust. Category 2 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 1G
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and gases, vapours or mists is present. Category 1 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a very high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 2G
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and gases, vapours or mists is present. Category 2 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 3G
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and gases, vapours or mists is present. Category 3 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a normal level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 1D
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and dust is present. Category 1 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a very high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 2D
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and dust is present. Category 2 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a high level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

Field.Name: 3D
Field.Description: Devices in this category are intended for use in areas in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture of air and dust is present. Category 3 comprises devices designed to be capable of functioning in conformity with the parameters specified by the manufacturer and ensuring a normal level of safety. (2014/34/EU)

DataType.Description: defines flags for the category of explosion zones for devices

Field.Name: Zone 0
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture with air of flammable substances in the form of gas, vapour or mist is present continuously or for long periods or frequently.

Field.Name: Zone 1
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture with air of flammable substances in the form of gas, vapour or mist is likely to occur in normal operation occasionally.

Field.Name: Zone 2
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere consisting of a mixture with air of flammable substances in the form of gas, vapour or mist is not likely to occur in normal operation but, if it does occur, will persist for a short period only.

Field.Name: Zone 20
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere in the form of a cloud of combustible dust in air is present continuously, for long periods or frequently.

Field.Name: Zone 21
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere in the form of a cloud of combustible dust in air is likely to occur in normal operation occasionally.

Field.Name: Zone 22
Field.Description: A zone in which an explosive atmosphere in the form of a cloud of combustible dust in air is not likely to occur in normal operation but, if it does occur, will persist for a short period only.

Variable.Description: The category property describes the Port type. The value of this attribute is user-defined. Only ports with the same category value are allowed to be connected.

Ports with the direction “In” can only be connected to ports with the direction “Out” or “InOut” and ports with the direction “Out” can only be connected with ports with the direction “In” or “InOut”. Ports with the direction “InOut” can be connected to Ports of arbitrary direction.
This property contains the ID of the asset to which the port is assigned.
